Dear Santa...

Dear Santa,

This year I've been busy!

In April I pulled over and changed 's flat tire (15 points). In October I stole 's purse (-30 points). In February I set 's puppy on fire (-66 points). Last Thursday I gave a kidney (1000 points). In July I put gum in 's hair (-12 points).

Overall, I've been nice (907 points). For Christmas I deserve a toy train!

Sincerely,
Bracanke

Today was fun... hehe. Actually today was a great day. First it is a tuesday which means I don't have class till 9:30 so I dont have to wake up till 9:00 if I want to. second, I had breakfast at the dinning center which was great, we actually have an awesome dinning center, everyone usually hates their school food but I really like mine so that was good. Then the next great thing was that I got a topic for my german research paper. I wasnt sure what I wanted to do so I gave my ideas of what I wanted to my prof. and she said I should go with homosexuality in germany so thats cool. So I got some books and started to research. Then after I got out of the library it was SNOWING!!!! yay SNOWING! i love snow! then I went to get sushi which william and I have decided is going to be our new tradition that the first snowfall of a winter is sushi day! yay! so then i went to a psych study, we have to have 4 credits of study participation, and this was my last one! and it was fun! it was an online chat where we chatted amongst others in the study in a little room w/o knowing which 4 other people in the room we were chatting with. We talked about political things like bush, nudists, oil, Iraq etc. Twas entertaining and everyone agreed with my ideas so that was also cool. Then I went to my room and called my mom which was fun, I signed up for a sushi class i am going to take tomorrow and then I ate free pizza and figured some stuff out about my schedual and then I went shopping at target and got some stuff for william for our 2 year anniversary which is going to be on Sunday! It is so windy out though! its crazy. and then william and I decided to go to the Adult emporium to check it out. man it was expensive, I guess MN buys more sex crap or something. but yeah so nothing was bought you sickos lol. and then oh! I bought a tree at target, its 6 feet tall! that might be too tall.... oh well... oh and umm yeah so thats neat. Then i came back to my dorm, went to see how william was and he made hot chocolate for me! it was fun and now i am in his room sipping hot chocolate! im happy! YAY!

HOW TO MAKE LOVE 

Ingredients: 

4 Laughing eyes 

4 Well-shaped legs 

4 Loving arms 

2 Firm milk containers 

2 Nuts 

1 Fur-lined mixing bowl 

1 Firm banana 

>> 

Directions: 

1. Look into laughing eyes. 

2. Spread well-shaped legs with loving arms. 

3. Squeeze and massage milk containers very gently. 

4 Gently add firm banana to mixing bowl, working in and out until 

well creamed. For best results. Continue to knead milk containers. 

5. As heat rises, plunge banana deep into mixing bowl and cover 

with nuts, leave to soak (preferably NOT overnight). 

6. The cake is done when banana is soft. If banana does not soften, 

repeat 4 steps 3-5 or change mixing bowls. 

>> 

Notes: 

1. If you are in an unfamiliar kitchen, wash utensils carefully 

before and after use. 

2. Do not lick mixing bowl after use. 

>>3. If cake rises, leave town

ok so this is a rant so here comes a <lj-cut text="live journal cut! yay. only read if you wanna read about weight things or something like that...">  so I was reading the schools paper and there was an article entitled "the skinny on being fat. I thought hmm... I'm fat wonder what it will say. well I read it and it was this 130lb girl that wears size 9 jeans saying that even though she was over-weight that she should be proud of who she is and be comfortable in her shoes. HAHA ok so shes 130 lbs... that may not be skinny but thats sure as hell not fat. I think i might write in cuz im close to 200lbs and im pretty finne with my body. I get what the girl was trying to convey but i think it was totally ridiculous to start the article by talking about how bad her body is because the whole article is supposed to be about liking your body. I realize that with standards like lindsay lohan(sp) and nicole richie(haha sp?) and how they are both now anorexic and girls for some reason think they need to be that way could cause things like this, but honestly how many people actually think they look better than when they weighed a normal weight? I dont thats for sure. Im sick of so many people talking about how gross they look or that they need to lose weight, and If your gunna try to lose weight you should at least be healthy about it and not just stop eating cuz then ya end up way grosser than before. I realize i need to lose weight for health reasons but i dont really care if i do for cosmetic reasons. I feel sexy in my own ways and i dont need to be 100lbs lighter just to feel hot because i like myself now. Sure i have my days where im like bleh but i am never like wtf anymore. People just need to take time to really notice things good in their life/ body and then they realize things are better. This is kinda weird though cuz i used to cut because i thought i was stupid and gross and it was the only way to make me feel. now i realize that i feel so much more and i can love myself. its cool. I think that everyone just needs to start focusing on the good and not the bad and people will reall realize how great they really are. </lj-cut> so that is that.
